.\bugs.md:23:The `sandbox-albert` working copies now include fixes for `BACKEND-H1`, `BACKEND-H3`, `BACKEND-H5`, `ITEM-MASTER-H2`, `ITEM-MASTER-H3`, `TRACKING-H2`, `FRONTEND-H2`, and `FRONTEND-H3`. The backend login token path no longer has a master-password bypass; backend AI proxy routes, item-master full-catalog route, and tracking lead-time routes now require `authRole(...)`. Backend selected-vendor persistence now writes to `RFQItem`; item-master item-number generation now uses bounded collision retries. Frontend role-marked routes now use `RoleGuard`, and the user-management route is admin-only.
.\bugs.md:175:- **Current status:** Remediated locally on `sandbox-albert`. `Customer.selectedVendor` now maps the payload and updates the matching `RFQItem` row, using `rfqItem_id` first and `rfqItem_style_number` as the fallback.
.\bugs.md:180:### BACKEND-H6 — `findRFQAddProductLayout` references an undefined variable
.\bugs.md:283:- **What it is:** In `checkRFQStyleNumber` and `checkItemHeaderItemNumber`, if a matching record exists, `priceCodeIsChecked` never becomes `true` and the `while` loop re-runs the same `findOne` query indefinitely.
.\bugs.md:285:- **Current status:** Remediated locally on `sandbox-albert`. Item-number generation now checks each candidate once against `itemHeader.item_num_id` and `RFQItem.rfqItem_style_number`, retries at most 25 times, and returns a 409-style response if every candidate collides.
.\bugs.md:397:- **What it is:** `logging: console.log` is set on the main RFQ grid query, `grid.service`, `std.service`, `getMerchGroup`, `getViewlayout`, `getAuditLog`, and several others.
.\bugs.md:483:### DATA-SYNCING-M2 — `productions.js` model is actually `RFQItemStatus` — no productions model exists
.\bugs.md:487:- **What it is:** `productions.js` calls `sequelize.define('RFQItemStatus', ...)` on `RFQItemStatus` table. `sequelize.define` now runs twice for the same model name. There is no actual productions model.
.\bugs.md:488:- **What it causes:** The `RFQItemStatus` model is registered twice (second silently wins). Any code expecting a `productions` model reference would fail.
.\bugs.md:600:### FRONTEND-M2 — Memory leak in RFQ and Manage Users components
.\bugs.md:605:- **What it causes:** Every visit to RFQ or Manage Users permanently leaks a subscription. The app grows slower and more memory-hungry the longer it's used. (Sibling components do this correctly — this is copy-paste drift.)
.\bugs.md:648:### BACKEND-L3 — Massive side-effecting copy-paste in `remapRFQItem`
.\bugs.md:650:- **File:** `helpers/utility.js` (throughout `remapRFQItem`/`mapRFQItem`)
.\bugs.md:799:- **What it is:** `.toPromise()` was deprecated in RxJS 7 and removed in RxJS 8. The stated standard is `firstValueFrom()`, and the RFQ module was converted, but 216 calls remain elsewhere.
.\bugs.md:823:- **What it is:** Seven services are assigned to `window[]` globals in the RFQ component constructor, and `rfq-copy-guard.ts` uses them as DI defaults. Documented in AGENTS.md as legacy and banned for new code.
.\bugs.md:824:- **What it causes:** If the RFQ page hasn't been visited first in a session, these globals are undefined and the fallback code crashes.
